<subSubSection id="65BA621856089F8C0C5D70E9477F6522" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D3E242D986F5379B14C5C2B74FF84F93" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E54EF9FC67DB06D675D2AACB471B7E4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
The new species 
<taxonomicName id="4EB1775B157C4D15427468F1D5D28318" genus="G." lsidName="G. longispora" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="longispora">
<emphasis id="D1195A584342A62F324B146EA6C6CD5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. longispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to five 
<taxonomicName id="A29558DC4095B7AC82D663209050BB2F" authorityName="Cavara" authorityYear="1894" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Gibellula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gibellula" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="762EAB3F6954023D6CA59EAD9806163A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Gibellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in having multi-synnemum and aspergillate, distinctly roughened conidiophores (Table 
<tableCitation id="2739B5E0CEBDB5FADCC7244FD00F2A2A" captionStart="Table 3" captionStartId="T3" captionText="Table 3. Comparison of the morphological characters of Gibellula longispora sp. nov. and related species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5B957FC99FB0E65058AA262CBD91CB64" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" tableUuid="5B957FC99FB0E65058AA262CBD91CB64">3</tableCitation>
), namely 
<taxonomicName id="F08145565D99AE6745E8FB55FA082ABB" genus="G." lsidName="G. pigmentosinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="pigmentosinum">
<emphasis id="293305C9636D38ACC84639242F012AB3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. pigmentosinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC4D61F5C5FAB1B74D5916423AD4179" genus="G." lsidName="G. flava" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis id="FB0668FC1D35ECBCABB93D05C5550C15" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B9A2C3580B9A3ED368EADE61EB813435" genus="G." lsidName="G. pulchra" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="AE8BE6846AA170F365DD02D8BD7D61BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1406A921FB20E75C9FF19AFB7A3D686C" genus="G." lsidName="G. clavispora" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="clavispora">
<emphasis id="C62DFBA65302B65A58FF988D3476DA71" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. clavispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Z.Q. Liang, Wan H. Chen &amp; Y.F. Han and 
<taxonomicName id="11414DCA4B36CDBFA589B6C47CFB58E9" genus="G." lsidName="G. shennongjiaensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="shennongjiaensis">
<emphasis id="D6544B32A90B04C1BAF0E891D070E6D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. shennongjiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
X. Zou, Wan H. Chen, Y.F. Han &amp; Z.Q. Liang. However, 
<taxonomicName id="C0C0E902E8D9EDC8B17FA08D9C21736E" genus="G." lsidName="G. longispora" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="longispora">
<emphasis id="9CDF38766FE0FC016A24D1DF2C724CAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. longispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4CCAEC0FB70826877B2B1FAEAF4C6F51" genus="G." lsidName="G. pigmentosinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="pigmentosinum">
<emphasis id="5D9FE3308D1B5E3F57CAB11061071361" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. pigmentosinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="113ACAFB2511B3CFC1C93E602E379D20" genus="G." lsidName="G. flava" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis id="03D2047E47D7232B06E7DA6F29E6494F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="973546C9B1D590BE09D2C50D5EA7AF44" genus="G." lsidName="G. pulchra" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="889A2CD014BD5446A06E850C289E222A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its longer, slender conidia. Furthermore, compared to 
<taxonomicName id="F5E5B8A4DC1843370F55C69EBF567B9E" genus="G." lsidName="G. longispora" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="longispora">
<emphasis id="1E7BE2DF2F0A32201C5AA6CAC440EE60" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. longispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species 
<taxonomicName id="1838DE14FFC7906C6D56BDD22FDB3631" genus="G." lsidName="G. shennongjiaensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="shennongjiaensis">
<emphasis id="A1D123987E9D229CFFCB417526076B7E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. shennongjiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has shorter conidiophores with smaller phialide and metulae and slightly smaller conidia, while 
<taxonomicName id="6795A62EA0449A5AFA21BB8D5594A4BD" genus="G." lsidName="G. clavispora" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="clavispora">
<emphasis id="CE4DC3124AFEE833301DA0D3D304ED8F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. clavispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears clavate conidia.
</paragraph>
